"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104spj1665702925503.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/spj1665702925503.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/spj1665702925503.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"spj1665702925503\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Tomcat Configuration\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Configuring Tomcat properly can result in significant performance improvements.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"spj1665702925503__p_d46772e1_d46773e1_d46774e1\">Use the following general guidelines:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"spj1665702925503__li_d23339e1_d23340e1_d23341e1\">Separate Web servers and servlet containers. Some servlet containers, such as Tomcat, can service both servlet requests and Web requests. However, it is preferable to use a dedicated Web server, and a dedicated servlet container. Tomcat provides plug-ins to allow it to work with other Web servers, such as Apache and IIS.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"spj1665702925503__li_d23342e1_d23343e1_d23344e1\">Use multiple instances of Tomcat when there are multiple processors. For example, a server might run one Apache server and three Tomcat servers. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vcs1665702924802.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vcs1665702924802.html\" title=\"Uniface uses Apache Tomcat as its default web server. It serves both static content, such as HTML pages and images, and dynamic content, such as JSPs and servlets (such as the Uniface WRD). However, it is not as fast for delivering static content as some other web servers. It is therefore preferable to use a dedicated web server for web requests and static content, and a dedicated servlet container such as Tomcat for dynamic content.\">Load Balancing with Tomcat</a>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"spj1665702925503__li_d23345e1_d23346e1_d23347e1\">Configure the JK plug-in to balance loads among Tomcat instances by modifying the <span class=\"ph filepath\">mod-jk.conf</span> file.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"spj1665702925503__li_d23348e1_d23349e1_d23350e1\">Tune Tomcat by editing the <span class=\"ph filepath\">server.xml</span> as follows:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"spj1665702925503__li_d23351e1_d23352e1_d23353e1\">Set <code class=\"ph codeph\">Reloadable=false</code> for each context. Otherwise, Tomcat checks for changes in classes, creating unnecessary processing overhead.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"spj1665702925503__li_d23354e1_d23355e1_d23356e1\">Set <code class=\"ph codeph\">liveDeploy=false</code> for the host. This setting creates a background thread to check for new Web application directories.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"spj1665702925503__li_d23357e1_d23358e1_d23359e1\">Set <code class=\"ph codeph\">debug=0</code> to prevent unnecessary logging\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"spj1665702925503__li_d23360e1_d23361e1_d23362e1\">Set <code class=\"ph codeph\">minProcessors=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Average number of concurrent requests</var>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"spj1665702925503__li_d23363e1_d23364e1_d23365e1\">Set <code class=\"ph codeph\">maxProcessors=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Twice the max number of concurrent requests</var>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"spj1665702925503__li_d23366e1_d23367e1_d23368e1\">Set <code class=\"ph codeph\">acceptCount= 10</code> to limit the number of requests that can be accepted. Do not set the number of accepted requests too high. It is better to deny requests than accept too many pending requests, thereby negatively affecting all requests\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"spj1665702925503__li_d23369e1_d23370e1_d23371e1\">Set <code class=\"ph codeph\">enableLookups=false</code> to prevent DNS lookups, which can add significant delays\n </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532104\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532104\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Tomcat Configuration Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Tomcat Configuration Configuring Tomcat properly can result in significant performance improvements. Use the following general guidelines: Separate Web servers and servlet containers. Some servlet containers, such as Tomcat, can service both servlet requests and Web requests. However, it is preferable to use a dedicated Web server, and a dedicated servlet container. Tomcat provides plug-ins to allow it to work with other Web servers, such as Apache and IIS. Use multiple instances of Tomcat when there are multiple processors. For example, a server might run one Apache server and three Tomcat servers. For more information, see Load Balancing with Tomcat . Configure the JK plug-in to balance loads among Tomcat instances by modifying the mod-jk.conf file. Tune Tomcat by editing the server.xml as follows: Set Reloadable=false for each context. Otherwise, Tomcat checks for changes in classes, creating unnecessary processing overhead. Set liveDeploy=false for the host. This setting creates a background thread to check for new Web application directories. Set debug=0 to prevent unnecessary logging Set minProcessors= Average number of concurrent requests Set maxProcessors= Twice the max number of concurrent requests Set acceptCount= 10 to limit the number of requests that can be accepted. Do not set the number of accepted requests too high. It is better to deny requests than accept too many pending requests, thereby negatively affecting all requests Set enableLookups=false to prevent DNS lookups, which can add significant delays Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}